    class Label {}

In PerlÂ 6, you can give for example loops a label, and use it to control that
loop (instead of the inner-most loop).

=begin code :skip-test
USERS:          # the label
for @users -> $u {
    for $u.pets -> $pet {
        # usage of a label
        next USERS if $pet.barks;
    }
    say "None of {$u}'s pets barks";
}
say USERS.^name;        # Label
=end code

Those label are objects of type C<Label>.

=head1 Methods

=head2 method next

Defined as:

    method next(Label:)

Usage:

=begin code :skip-test
next LABEL
=end code

Begin the next iteration of the loop associated with the label.

=head2 method last

Defined as:

    method last(Label:)

Usage:

=begin code :skip-test
last LABEL
=end code

Terminate the execution of the loop associated with the label.

